            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I was in this school boarding for hardly a yr in1997 , all i can tell is those were the worst days of my childhood and I still get haunted when I think about those days I spent here in this school boarding. The brothers and head master were only to support for the the elite or those who come from a well to do families, shame on them today I am thriving in my work and have everything what one can ask for but then my mother being a single mother tried hard to give us the best education possible but these so called non profitable Christen institutie had no value for you if you come from a humble background I took a lot of beating from the fellow kids as they were mostly failures and older in age remind you I was in 6th standard what could I have done but just cried every day I gave up studies , sports and probably was in depression for a long time , I hope this is not practised here anymore",
          "publisher": {
